47780edc-5db4-42d2-aa29-489fe933def4.cell_isolation: Cells were stained with fluorochrome labeled antibodies and then sorted on a BD FACSAria II flow cytometer
47780edc-5db4-42d2-aa29-489fe933def4.cell_processing_protocol: Fresh PBMCs were stimulated with whole GAD, live CD4+ CD154+ CD69+ cells single cell sorted into 96-well plates contaning RNAse-DNase-free PBS, snap-frozen in dry ice and stored at -80C until RT-PCR and PCR procedures

d96a7f8e-debd-4793-864d-772def6af483.library_generation_protocol: Sorted cells. Then cDNA was synthesized directly from single cells using qScript cDNA Supermix (Quanta Biosciences). A first round of PCR was done on all cDNA using TATAA GrandMaster Mix in the presence of a mix of 31 tagged (HTSP-“tag”) variable region primers covering all subgroups of TCR Vα and Vβ genes, an alpha constant region primer, a beta constant region primer and 96 primers for preamplification of 48 genes of interest, including cytokines, transcription factors, chemokines and lineage markers. A second round PCR was performed separately for TCRA and TCRB on 3 μl of the first round product, using the HTSP-“tag”-primer and a nested constant region primer (for alpha or beta, depending on the PCR reaction), with Takara ExTaq. The PCR products were Sanger sequenced using the HTSP-tag primer

A first round of PCR was done on all cDNA using TATAA GrandMaster Mix in the presence of a mix of 31 tagged (HTSP-“tag”) variable region primers covering all subgroups of TCR Vα and Vβ genes, an alpha constant region primer, a beta constant region primer and 96 primers for preamplification of 48 genes of interest, including cytokines, transcription factors, chemokines and lineage markers. A second round PCR was performed separately for TCRA and TCRB on 3 μl of the first round product, using the HTSP-“tag”-primer and a nested constant region primer (for alpha or beta, depending on the PCR reaction), with Takara ExTaq. The PCR products were Sanger sequenced using the HTSP-tag primer
